{"id":"project-LICHEN-byto","title":"Statistics counters can wrap without detection","description":"File: lichen/subsys/lichen/meshcore/adapter.c
Lines: 1080, 1129, etc.

All statistics counters in lichen_meshcore_adapter_stats are uint32_t:
```c
struct lichen_meshcore_adapter_stats {
    uint32_t raw_count;
    uint32_t stream_frame_count;
    uint32_t supported_count;
    ...
};
```

These counters are incremented without overflow detection:
- Line 1080: adapter->stats.raw_count++;
- Line 1129: adapter->stats.malformed_count++;
- etc.

On a long-running system processing many messages, counters could wrap (at ~4 billion), making statistics misleading. For example, malformed_count wrapping from UINT32_MAX to 0 would hide a high error rate.

This is low severity for most use cases, but consider:
1. Using uint64_t for counters
2. Adding overflow flags
3. Documenting the wrap behavior","status":"open","priority":4,"issue_type":"bug","owner":"me@mark.atwood.name","created_at":"2026-07-12T06:46:47.875644Z","created_by":"Mark Atwood","updated_at":"2026-07-12T06:46:47.875674Z"}

